"death","end_year":1835,"children_ids":["T01061","T01062","T01063","T01064","T01065","T01066","T01067","T01068"]}],"tags":["politician","deacon","tankerhoosen"],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"career","header":"Helped write the Connecticut Constitution of 1818","body":"Deacon Phineas Talcott of Vernon served in the Connecticut General Assembly for many sessions and was one of the delegates who formed the Connecticut State Constitution of 1818 — the document that replaced the colonial charter of 1662 and separated church from state. His wife Hannah died just nineteen days after him, on January 5, 1836."},{"number":2,"category":"legacy","header":"His granddaughter founded a Japanese college","body":"Through his son Ralph, co-founder of Rockville, Connecticut, came granddaughter Eliza Talcott — founder of Kobe College in Japan. The deacon’s line ran from Bolton’s meetinghouse to Meiji-era missionary education in two generations."}],"sources":[{"label":"Talcott Pedigree 1876"}],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"quotes":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"statues":[],"bio":{"title":"Deacon","first_name":"Phineas","last_name":"Talcott","married_names":[],"display_name":"Deacon Phineas Talcott","photo_url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1777496092/phineastalcott_f247rg.png","bio_blurb":"Bolton deacon; 1818 Constitution delegate"},"military_service":[],"career":[{"role":"State legislator","organization":"Connecticut"},{"role":"Delegate","organization":"Connecticut Constitutional Convention","start_year":1818}],"slug":"phineas-talcott-1758"},"T01061":{"id":"T01061","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":true,"has_descendants_documented":false,"gender":"female","birth":{"year":1791,"city":"Bolton","county":"Tolland","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1866,"month":1,"day":1,"state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"burial":{},"residence":{"state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":true,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_john_talcott":6,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_paths_to_thomas":0,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":true,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{"father_id":"T01031","mother_id":"I00195"},"marriages":[],"tags":["needs_research"],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"narrative_blocks":[],"quotes":[],"sources":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"statues":[],"bio":{"first_name":"Hannah","last_name":"Talcott","married_names":[],"display_name":"Hannah Talcott"},"military_service":[],"slug":"hannah-talcott-t01061"},"T01062":{"id":"T01062","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":true,"gender":"male","birth":{"year":1793,"month":8,"day":7,"city":"Vernon","county":"Tolland","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1863,"month":6,"day":6,"city":"Rockville","county":"Tolland","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States","cause":"head injury — fall on street, concussion of brain"},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM116","plot_notes":"Elmwood Cemetery Vernon CT. Buried at side of wife Lora, whom he had mourned for 31 years."},"residence":{"city":"Rockville","county":"Tolland","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":true,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_john_talcott":6,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_paths_to_thomas":0,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":true,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":true,"notable_category":["business","politics"],"notable_blurb":"Founded American Mills; probate judge; state senator","primary_url":"https://www.tankerhoosen.info/history/talcott_phineas.htm","primary_url_label":"Tankerhoosen.info"},"parents":{"father_id":"T01031","mother_id":"I00195"},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"I00197","date_year":1823,"date_month":11,"date_day":17,"location_city":"Vernon","location_state":"Connecticut","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death_of_spouse","end_year":1835,"children_ids":["T01071","T01072"]}],"institutions":[{"institution_id":"INST079","institution_blurb":"Steward 1828-1835; helped pioneer moral care with Eli Todd."}],"landmarks":[{"landmark_id":"LM045","landmark_blurb":"He donated the land; became Talcott Park after his death."}],"tags":["politician","educator","railroad","judge"],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"career","header":"Steward of America's pioneering psychiatric hospital","body":"From 1828 to 1835, Phineas Talcott Jr. served as steward of the Hartford Retreat for the Insane, one of only four such facilities in the country. He worked alongside Dr. Eli Todd, the first superintendent, helping develop a program of moral care that achieved the highest cure rate in the nation. His wife Lora was the beloved matron; she died at the Retreat in 1835."},{"number":2,"category":"career","header":"Senator, judge, and mill president at once","body":"Phineas served as Rockville's judge of probate for sixteen years across four terms, Connecticut State Senator in 1851, and president of the Rockville Railroad Company — while simultaneously running the American Mills, the Savings Bank of Rockville, the Aqueduct Company, and two mill interests. His home's left wing was his courtroom."},{"number":3,"category":"character","header":"Rode west on horseback after losing Lora","body":"After Lora's death in January 1835, he and his brother Ralph rode west on horseback in November — Buffalo to Sandusky, then on to Quincy, Illinois, prospecting for land. He bought no property and returned to Rockville, where within fifteen months he had become agent of the Rock Manufacturing Company under his father-in-law Francis McLean."},{"number":4,"category":"death","header":"Died of a fall, buried beside Lora","body":"Phineas Talcott Jr. died June 6, 1863 when a fall on the street caused a concussion of the brain. He was described as 'a man of heavy weight and commanding figure.' He was buried at the side of his wife Lora in Elmwood Cemetery — she had died 31 years earlier, and he had never remarried."}],"sources":[{"label":"Commemorative Biographical Record of Tolland and Windham Counties CT, 1903, p.102"},{"label":"Tankerhoosen Valley History — Phineas Talcott Jr.","url":"https://www.tankerhoosen.info/images/talcott_phineas_jr_1.jpg"},{"label":"Vernon Historical Society"}],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"quotes":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"statues":[],"bio":{"first_name":"Phineas","last_name":"Talcott","married_names":[],"suffix":"Jr.","display_name":"Phineas Talcott Jr.","photo_url":"https://www.tankerhoosen.info/images/talcott_phineas_jr_1.jpg","photo_notes":"Portrait. Tankerhoosen Valley History."},"military_service":[],"education":[],"career":[],"slug":"phineas-talcott-jr-1793"},"I00197":{"id":"I00197","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"gender":"female","birth":{"year":1802,"month":10,"day":19,"city":"Vernon","county":"Tolland","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1835,"month":1,"day":7,"city":"Hartford","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM116","plot_notes":"Elmwood Cemetery Vernon CT. Phineas mourned her for 31 years and was buried at her side in 1863."},"residence":{"city":"Hartford","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_paths_to_thomas":0,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{"father_name":"Francis McLean","mother_name":"Roxy (Roxey) McKinney McLean","father_research_notes":"Francis McLean — built the Rock Mill (first large mill on the Hockanum River) and was one of the founders of Rockville CT. \"One of the best-known men of his time.\" Memoir written in his old age describes Lora's upbringing.","mother_research_notes":"Roxey McKinney from Ellington CT."},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"T01062","date_year":1823,"date_month":11,"date_day":17,"location_city":"Vernon","location_state":"Connecticut","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death","end_year":1835,"children_ids":["T01071","T01072"]}],"institutions":[{"institution_id":"INST079","institution_blurb":"Matron of Hartford Retreat for the Insane, 1828-1835. Patients called her \"Good Mother Talcott.\""}],"tags":["educator"],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"character","header":"'Good Mother Talcott' — beloved matron at Retreat","body":"From 1828 to 1835 she served as matron of the Hartford Retreat for the Insane — described as 'a small-sized, delicate woman of fine fastidious tastes, yet very efficient.' The inmates called her 'Good Mother Talcott.'"},{"number":2,"category":"marriage","header":"Husband mourned her for thirty-one years","body":"Her husband Phineas — later a Connecticut state senator, probate judge, and founder of the American Mills — never remarried after her death in 1835. He was buried at her side in Elmwood Cemetery thirty-one years later."},{"number":3,"category":"education","header":"Educated at Catherine Beecher's Hartford Female Seminary","body":"She studied at Miss Catherine Beecher's Hartford Female Seminary in the 1820s — among the earliest experiments in women's higher learning in America. Her education there equipped her for the demanding role of matron when her husband became steward in 1828."},{"number":4,"category":"death","header":"Her gravestone now stands on Cliff Street","body":"Her original gravestone was moved from Elmwood Cemetery to Phineas's farm above Rockville when a consolidated family monument was built. The stone now stands on private property on Cliff Street — broken but still legible."}],"sources":[{"label":"Connecticut Courant — death notice, January 1835"},{"label":"Tankerhoosen — Phineas Talcott Jr. & Lora McLean","url":"https://www.tankerhoosen.info/history/talcott_phineas.htm"}],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"quotes":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"statues":[],"bio":{"first_name":"Lora","last_name":"Talcott","maiden_name":"McLean","married_names":["Talcott"],"display_name":"Lora McLean Talcott"},"military_service":[],"education":[],"career":[],"slug":"lora-mclean-1802"},"T01071":{"id":"T01071","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"gender":"male","birth":{"year":1824,"month":12,"day":27,"city":"Hartford","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1849,"month":9,"day":2,"city":"Rockville","county":"Tolland","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM116","plot_notes":"Elmwood Cemetery Vernon CT. Died in his father's home in Rockville."},"residence":{"city":"Rockville","county":"Tolland","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":true,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_john_talcott":6,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_paths_to_thomas":0,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":true,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{"father_id":"T01062","mother_id":"I00197"},"marriages":[],"tags":["needs_research"],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"narrative_blocks":[],"quotes":[],"sources":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"statues":[],"bio":{"first_name":"Frederick","last_name":"Talcott","married_names":[],"display_name":"Frederick Talcott"},"military_service":[],"slug":"frederick-talcott-1824"},"T01072":{"id":"T01072","former_ids":[],"has_descendants_documented":false,"gender":"male","birth":{"year":1827,"month":1,"day":20,"city":"Hartford","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1919,"month":7,"day":16,"city":"Rockville","county":"Tolland","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM117","plot_notes":"Grove Hill Cemetery Rockville CT. FindAGrave confirms. Plot shared with wife Rosanna."},"residence":{"city":"Rockville","county":"Tolland","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":true,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_john_talcott":6,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_paths_to_thomas":0,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":true,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":true,"notable_category":["business"],"notable_blurb":"Fifty-one years president of Rockville’s bank"},"parents":{"father_id":"T01062","mother_id":"I00197"},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"I00198","date_month":1,"date_day":1,"location_state":"Connecticut","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death_of_spouse","end_year":1875,"children_ids":[]}],"tags":["businessman","railroad","tankerhoosen","banker"],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"career","header":"President of the same bank for 51 years","body":"George Talcott served as president of the First National Bank of Rockville for 51 years, while also serving as president of the American Mills — the same enterprise his father Phineas had built. He was also vice president of the Savings Bank of Rockville and a Justice of the Peace. He died in 1919 aged 92, having outlived his wife Rosanna by 44 years."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"His mother died when he was seven","body":"Lora Talcott died in January 1835, leaving George motherless at seven; he grew up to lead Rockville’s First National Bank for fifty-one years. When his wife Rosanna died in 1875 he never remarried, outliving her by forty-four years and reaching ninety-two."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[{"label":"FindAGrave — George Talcott"},{"label":"Tankerhoosen Valley History — Talcott Family","url":"https://www.tankerhoosen.info"}],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"statues":[],"is_placeholder":false,"bio":{"first_name":"George","last_name":"Talcott","married_names":[],"display_name":"George Talcott","photo_url":"https://images.findagrave.com/photos/2017/55/27377278_1488063150.jpg","photo_notes":"Portrait. FindAGrave."},"military_service":[],"career":[{"role":"President, 51 years","organization":"First National Bank of Rockville"},{"role":"President","organization":"American Mills"},{"role":"Vice President","organization":"Savings Bank of Rockville"}],"slug":"george-talcott-1827"},"T01063":{"id":"T01063","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":true,"gender":"male","birth":{"year":1795,"month":9,"day":17,"city":"Vernon","county":"Tolland","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1847,"month":4,"day":30,"city":"Rockville","county":"Tolland","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM116","plot_notes":"Elmwood Cemetery Vernon CT. FindAGrave confirms."},"residence":{"city